1) Download IDE as zip file

2) Extract IDE zip file

3) Open STS.exe / eclipse.exe file

4) Choose Workspace (location to store our projects)

5) Create Java Project

   -> File -> New -> Java Project -> Give Project Name -> Finish

   -> IN java project we are able to below two folders

          - src (source files --> .java files we will create under src directory)

          - bin (binaries --> .class files will be stored in bin directory)
		  
		  
		 
  -> Once project created then we can create our programs / classes in that project

Note: One project can contain any no.of classes

      -> Goto src directory --> Right click on src --> select new --> select class --> Give Classname ---> Finish

      -> We can pass commandline arguments also in IDE

Right Click on Program --> Run as -> Run Configurations -> Arguments -> Program Variables --> Enter Variables with space -> Apply --> Finish		 
		  
		  
===========================================================================
                    shortcuts for sts/eclipse
----------------------------------------------------------------------------					

ctrl + M               to maximise and minimise the screen

ctrl + D               to delete the line

ctrl + shift + enter   to add a new blank line

ctrl + shift + F      for allignment of program or formating of code

ctrl +/-              for increase and decrease the font size

ctrl + shift + r      to find a file in workspace

ctrl + shift + t      for opening pre-defined classes which are available (for jar file)

ctrl + w              to close opened file

ctrl + shift + w      to close all the opened file at a time

ctrl + shift + o      to organise the imports statements
 
ctrl + /              to comment single line or un-commenting

ctrl + shift + /      to comment multiple lines (first select multiple lines where we have to comment then press ctrl+shift+/)

alt + shift + sr      to generate getters and setters

alt + shift + ss      to generate two string methods

alt + shift + so      to generate constructor

ctrl + o              to display all the variables in the class(complete outline of the class we can see)

ctrl + shift + p      to go to the closing bracket directly

crtl + 1 + enter      to get the return statement of method

ctrl + q              directly go to previously edited palce

alt + shift + z       to surround or add try catch block (select the code then press alt+shift+z)
 
alt + shift + R       to rename or refactor (select and change the name then at a time all the palces names will be changed)

alt + shift + t       to open the context - sensetive refactoring menu.
